Day 7: SQL – DQL & Filtering

Topic:
SQL Data Query Language (DQL) and Data Filtering

Learning Objectives:

Understand how to retrieve data using SELECT statements
Learn filtering techniques using WHERE conditions
Practice logical operators such as AND, OR, and NOT
Explore filtering methods using BETWEEN, IN, and LIKE
Learn sorting and limiting results with ORDER BY and LIMIT
Understand the use of DISTINCT to remove duplicate records

Activities / Deliverables:

Write and execute 15 different SELECT queries on VolyoDB
Practice filtering records with multiple conditions
Use pattern matching with LIKE operator
Sort records in ascending and descending order
Retrieve limited and unique records using LIMIT and DISTINCT
Complete a mini quiz based on SQL syntax and query writing

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8
MySQL Workbench

